##Love during the epidemic

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Love is always love, the closer to life and death, the more intense love. The new crown pneumonia epidemic forced the break of time, bringing the essence of everyday life to the surface between isolation, emptiness, and birth and death. Love at the time of the outbreak was different than it had been before or since.
It took him three hours to buy a cake before the city was shut down
February 2nd is my wedding anniversary with my husband. The county seat we're in is about to close. In the afternoon, all gas stations are closed, and at eight o'clock in the evening, the traffic lights turn red and the roads are closed. Upon hearing the news, my husband had lunch, put on two masks and went out.
He drove the car from the southern end of the county to the northern end, complete circle, almost through all the core street. Businesses are closed, only the road patrol police, scattered can see a few cars. Linxiang on the ninth day of the first lunar month is as deserted as an empty city.
My husband and I are college classmates, graduated to work together in Shenzhen, feelings into fruit, also through efforts to have their own small home. On our one-year anniversary, my brother bought us a cake. It was not big, but we were very happy.
My husband and I found a milk tea shop to sit down, put a candle made a wish, holding the cake took a photo. Every anniversary, he said, he would buy a cake, take a picture, take 70 pictures. We've been together for over nine years, and we've recorded every important moment with a sense of ritual.
Photo | one year anniversary
We had planned to spend our wedding anniversary in a romantic restaurant in Shenzhen, but now we are stuck in the city. He walked around the county and saw five or six bakeries, from the heart of the street to the back alley, all closed.
Finally, he returned to the front of his familiar bakery. The door was locked, and he left a phone number. He tried to call and ask if there was any cake. "I can make one for you, but it will take an hour. "
So he added Wechat, choose style, wait in the car for more than an hour, buy back this hard-won cake.
The moment he came through the door with the cake, I jumped for joy like a child, and felt as if I had seen my mother come back from the market with a basket full of snacks when I was a child in the mountains. Soon, happiness turns to worry.
Even with the double mask and being in the car almost the whole time, I was afraid he'd run into someone infected. If I had another chance, I wouldn't let him risk going out there. After all, what matters is that we stay together. I said: "I regret, I should not let you out, really scared. "

I'M GONNA go with the takeout Knight
The company told me to go to work on the 10th day of the first lunar month. I came back on the 9th. As a result, the tenth day was told to delay going to work. I was living in a rented house, eating my mother's food every day. A few days later, I started to order in.
There is a rice noodle shop open nearby, I ate for two days in a row, the delivery is the same delivery boy. On the third day. He was the one who took the call. He added my Wechat, asked me about the situation, know I am in the field, often ask how I am, send me fruit for breakfast.
In such a dangerous time, he brought me food three times a day, and gave me his cat to accompany me, so we are together.

Li Meng

He's so sloppy, and I can't wait to get married
My boyfriend and I usually in Jinan, because some things at home, years ago a week he returned home, said years later to come back early with me. Unexpectedly, the next day, there was a patient in Jinan.
January 24, the hospital organization to help Hubei, I wanted to sign up, he would not, crying in the phone begging me. I said, "nurses are doctors. It's my job. ". He said, your duty is to save me, if anything happens to you, I will die.
I hung up the phone and my eyes were swollen from crying. The head nurse saw, let me be at ease in the hospital, Comfort said, service Jinan people is also dedicated.
In 2018, we were together. When we first met at the World Trade Center, there was a long line at the restaurant. My stomach is growling with hunger. He said he had to go out, and when he came back, he had a bag of snacks.
He is like this, mouth, but always with the actual action to prove love, although sometimes very straight, but also slowly become careful, for me a little change.
I remember last year, on my birthday, we had dinner and walked through Jinan Square holding hands. There were proposals in the square, candles in the shape of hearts, arches and balloons. Someone gave us a bunch of glow sticks to help heckle.
Everything is ready. The hero calls his wife, but she never shows up. The crowd dispersed slowly.
He suddenly stood in someone else's circle of candles, holding a glow stick said to marry me, take care of me, take me to see the great mountains and rivers, asked me if I would marry him. I mean, that's just sloppy. He said he would make a big proposal. I was kind of looking forward to it.
The situation in Jinan is getting worse and worse. I didn't want to bother my family, so I stayed in the hospital. In fact, I am very timid, see too many patients, afraid of their own infection. He called me every day, talked to me, texted me when he didn't get it. Every time I see his message, I am very touched, always can regain confidence.
We had a rare chance to video-chat, and one night, a kid at the hospital was diagnosed. He's so young. There's so much more to come. I feel bad, dare not cry in front of the child's face, so the initiative and boyfriend video.
In the video, his hair looks like a chicken coop, already thin, a few days do not see, the face is thin concave. I asked him if he wasn't eating properly, and he denied it, munching away on the screen. I'm a little sad.
The longer I was in the hospital, the more I was touched, until I became a little pessimistic, feeling that life was short and uncertain, and I didn't know which would come first, tomorrow or the accident. Sometimes I have to call him even if I can't eat. The more he encouraged me, the more I let him down.
Under such circumstances, he proposed to me on Wechat. All of a sudden, without warning. I still thought he was sloppy, but I knew he was a big part of what kept me going. And then he bought a diamond ring.
Photo | wechat proposal
By next Valentine's Day, we'll be married. I want to go to Disneyland, I heard that the fireworks there are very beautiful, in the fireworks and the most loved people embrace together, is a very beautiful thing.

The pomp and circumstance of an anniversary
Our anniversary's in three days, and I can't wait. February 10, taking advantage of the lunch break, I took the express box to make a sign, came to the county hospital outside, to his wife Wechat, let her spare time to the hospital gate to see. A few moments later, a figure appeared at the door of the isolation tent, wearing a mask, goggles, and large protective clothing. I know. That's her.
I held up the sign, as I had done so many years before at the train station. The sign says: Happy Second Anniversary! Waiting for you to come home!
Visiting at the hospital entrance
The distance was too great for the wife to read the words on it. So I yelled, happy second anniversary, waiting for you to come home! She heard me and waved to me. It was the first time we had seen each other since the first day of the Lunar New Year. It lasted less than five minutes.
My wife and I are from the same village. We met as children and got married after graduation. She was my age and a nurse at the county hospital's intensive-care unit.
After the outbreak, she volunteered to support the Wuhan medical team, the hospital took into account her age, the first two groups did not choose her. But I do know that if there's another group, if it's up to her, she'll keep signing up.
Our married life, we've been apart a lot. I remember last year this time, I was building a subway in Hangzhou. I wanted to make a video call with her on the night of the anniversary to celebrate, but something came up at the construction site, and I had to go, and I couldn't even get back to her on Wechat.
I still feel that I owe her, thinking of the next anniversary with her. He stayed on until August and quit. In September, I returned to the county seat and worked as a delivery boy for JD.com logistics. After all, there's nothing like a family.
Back in the county seat, the moment did not get much richer. I go out early in the morning and come home at night, and she often has to work the night shift.
Still, living in Hitotsu Yane no Shita, even when she wasn't home, I could feel her breath and the warmth of home. The food in the fridge, the clothes in the sun, the shoes in her closet, the books she kept neatly in her shoes, the folded pages on her bedside table, were all signs of a life together.
Before marriage, she couldn't cook. After the wedding, she has been using the time off after the night shift, in the online school cooking, including those I love to eat pasta, steamed dumplings, steamed dumplings, fried steamed buns and so on.
Probably because she was worried that she wasn't doing a good enough job, she didn't give it to me right away. Instead, she tried to taste it, taste it, change it, adjust the heat, make it light and salty, and we were all working so hard that I didn't have a chance to sit down until today, enjoy her cooking.
Photo | Zhang Jiapeng's circle of friends
Since the outbreak, other couriers in the county have stopped. I get up at 5:40 every day and get to work around 7:00. Special period, express are urgently needed, in addition to masks, disinfectant and other protective products, mostly rice flour, grain and oil, milk powder, diapers and other necessities of life, half-minute delay can not, the daily average number of express delivery more than 100 pieces.

Even if I feel tired occasionally, I don't feel so hard at the thought of her being in the hospital. We weren't overly sentimental, she just told me to protect myself, wear glasses, wash my hands frequently and pay more attention.
This seems to form a special kind of tacit understanding, between the words do not need to fill the sweet. I knew she was fighting on the front line, and I acted as her "foreign aid. ". For the first time in our lives, we may have a common enemy.
The other day, we were talking about what happened after the outbreak. I said I wanted to take her for a walk. She said she would like to go to the supermarket, eat hot pot... ... talked a lot, and finally said: "must give you a good meal. "

Wang Xin

"If you don't come home, I won't take my medicine and I'll die. "
As expected, I went home with my boyfriend this Spring Festival and got engaged in early February. This is the ninth year since we met, the House has been settled, I quit my job at the end of June, left Wuhan, got married in July, everything should have been in place.
I didn't care about the outbreak until the Monday before the holiday, when a colleague told me that her cousin was working in the hospital and that it was serious.
The next day, I began to cough, read the news on the Internet, decided not to go back. At that time afraid of family and boyfriend worry, did not tell them, just said the ticket home did not buy, a few days late.
On January 23rd, the city of Wuhan was closed. My boyfriend called and told me to go home. By then, I had a fever, a temperature of 38.7 degrees, was too scared to go to the hospital, and took my medication at home.
The phone call lasted two hours, and I used to think that crying over the phone was just part of the movie and the show, and now it's my turn. I had the phone in my hand, and the screen was wet, and I actually said, if I don't make it, you forget about me.
The boyfriend is introverted, usually not good at expressing, what not to say sweetly words, but occasionally the behavior can let me surprise.
I remember the first Valentine's Day we spent, we had a date to go shopping for dinner, the restaurant was booked, and that morning, he suddenly said that there is something at home, let me go to the restaurant first, he finished to come.
It was the seventh day of the Lunar New Year, the weather was very cold, the streets are full of lovers, I alone around the streets, the more I want to get angry. Wait half an hour at the restaurant, don't text him back.
At this time, the restaurant to promote the puppet came up to me, holding a cardboard box, let me draw a prize. I pulled out a piece of paper that said, hug the puppet. I was stunned for a moment, the puppet took off his hood, and my boyfriend stood smiling in front of me.
Not long after I hung up, I got another call from my boyfriend's mother. This just know, when we call, he is packing, want to come to Wuhan to look for me, have already left home now. On the phone, he didn't say anything about it.
I could feel my boyfriend's mother's sadness and despair. I was afraid that I wouldn't be able to hold it together. I called him and said, "If you don't come home, I won't take the medicine and wait to die. ".
That night, the Blue Light Shimmered through the curtains. I leaned out the window and saw the ambulance parked in the yard, and a couple of doctors in Hazmat suits pulling people onto it.
That was the first time I ever saw a doctor in a hazmat suit. It used to be through the news, that you had a vague idea of how bad it was, but there was always a network, like it was another world. At the moment I saw it, a shudder rose from the sole of my foot to the crest. The body doesn't seem to have to go through the brain to feel that fear.
I was now fully aware that I was in the middle of the storm, alone and with no place to hide. At this point, the cough seems to be getting worse.
At night, I dream. Someone tried to kill me, grabbed me by the neck, I fought, I tried to run, I couldn't get out.
The next morning, I got up to boil the noodles and fry the eggs. The appetite is very bad, the egg took two bites, the noodles hardly moved, forced himself to drink the soup. A colleague called, said there was a confirmed diagnosis in the company, asked me about the situation. I was afraid. I claimed I was all right. Hang up the phone, curl up in a ball, get soaked, and have trouble breathing.
My boyfriend called, tried to make me feel better. He consulted the medical students, also looked up information on the Internet, let me raise the pillow, sit up, this will feel better.
I feel very disappointing, and he said that on the want to cry. He kept cajoling me, our past events, and the future of life, but also from my parents to find my childhood story book, Page by page to tell me.
I leaned against the wall, listened to his voice, tried not to think about anything else, and felt like a child again.
Screenshots of chat
Once upon a time, I didn't believe in some kind of psychic power. Now I know, from his company, Encouragement and comfort... although these mental strength can not cure my disease, but can be dispelled fear and panic, let me courage to face everything.
I took the initiative to report to the community, through the online volunteers into the treatment group. The doctor said that my condition is not serious, coupled with young, strong resistance, on time to take medicine, maintain a good state of mind, will be able to withstand.
Valentine's Day is coming up. I want to knit a sweater for my boyfriend. He was thin, cold in winter, and always had a cold. I said I'd knit him a sweater, but I never got around to it. I haven't done it in three years. When I'm well, it's the most important thing I can do.

It was the seventh day of the Lunar New Year, the weather was very cold, the streets are full of lovers, I alone around the streets, the more I want to get angry. Wait half an hour at the restaurant, don't text him back.

At this time, the restaurant to promote the puppet came up to me, holding a cardboard box, let me draw a prize. I pulled out a piece of paper that said, hug the puppet. I was stunned for a moment, the puppet took off his hood, and my boyfriend stood smiling in front of me.

Not long after I hung up, I got another call from my boyfriend's mother. This just know, when we call, he is packing, want to come to Wuhan to look for me, have already left home now. On the phone, he didn't say anything about it.

I could feel my boyfriend's mother's sadness and despair. I was afraid that I wouldn't be able to hold it together. I called him and said, "If you don't come home, I won't take the medicine and wait to die. ".

That night, the Blue Light Shimmered through the curtains. I leaned out the window and saw the ambulance parked in the yard, and a couple of doctors in Hazmat suits pulling people onto it.

That was the first time I ever saw a doctor in a hazmat suit. It used to be through the news, that you had a vague idea of how bad it was, but there was always a network, like it was another world. At the moment I saw it, a shudder rose from the sole of my foot to the crest. The body doesn't seem to have to go through the brain to feel that fear.

I was now fully aware that I was in the middle of the storm, alone and with no place to hide. At this point, the cough seems to be getting worse.

At night, I dream. Someone tried to kill me, grabbed me by the neck, I fought, I tried to run, I couldn't get out.

The next morning, I got up to boil the noodles and fry the eggs. The appetite is very bad, the egg took two bites, the noodles hardly moved, forced himself to drink the soup. A colleague called, said there was a confirmed diagnosis in the company, asked me about the situation. I was afraid. I claimed I was all right. Hang up the phone, curl up in a ball, get soaked, and have trouble breathing.

My boyfriend called, tried to make me feel better. He consulted the medical students, also looked up information on the Internet, let me raise the pillow, sit up, this will feel better.

I feel very disappointing, and he said that on the want to cry. He kept cajoling me, our past events, and the future of life, but also from my parents to find my childhood story book, Page by page to tell me.

I leaned against the wall, listened to his voice, tried not to think about anything else, and felt like a child again.

Once upon a time, I didn't believe in some kind of psychic power. Now I know, from his company, Encouragement and comfort... although these mental strength can not cure my disease, but can be dispelled fear and panic, let me courage to face everything.

I took the initiative to report to the community, through the online volunteers into the treatment group. The doctor said that my condition is not serious, coupled with young, strong resistance, on time to take medicine, maintain a good state of mind, will be able to withstand.

Valentine's Day is coming up. I want to knit a sweater for my boyfriend. He was thin, cold in winter, and always had a cold. I said I'd knit him a sweater, but I never got around to it. I haven't done it in three years. When I'm well, it's the most important thing I can do.
